        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 13 at 4:54PM EDT until August 13 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over New Preston, or
7 miles north of New Milford, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Torrington, New Milford, Thomaston, Kent, Litchfield, Northwest
Harwinton, New Preston, Terryville, Cornwall Bridge, Plymouth,
Harwinton, Bethlehem, Washington, Goshen, Morris, Warren, Cornwall,
Bantam, South Norfolk, and West Torrington.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
